## Local (Postgres)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/parkflow"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/parkflow"

## Supabase (recomendado com Prisma)
# - DATABASE_URL: pooler/pgbouncer (runtime)
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1&sslmode=require"
# - IMPORTANTE: no pooler o usuÃ¡rio nÃ£o costuma ser `postgres` e sim `postgres.<project-ref>` (copie exatamente do Supabase).
# - Se a senha tiver caracteres especiais, faÃ§a URL-encode antes de colar.
# - DIRECT_URL: conexão direta (migrations / seed)
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.supabase.com:5432/postgres"

## App
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL="http://127.0.0.1:3001/api"
JWT_SECRET="change-me"
CORS_ORIGIN="http://localhost:3000"

